This counts the number of “Yes” entries from the first data row (row 4) down to the current row. If the current cell in column F is not “Yes”, it returns 0. We will write this formula into every cell of column G from row 4 down to the last used row, preserving any existing values elsewhere. After saving, we will call `recalculate` and then reload the workbook to verify that column G now contains the expected numbers.
